{{refimprove|date=April 2014}} <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Cooperative Institute for Limnology and Ecosystems Research (logo).jpg|right]] --> The '''Cooperative Institute for Limnology and Ecosystems Research''' (CILER) fosters research collaborations between the [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] (NOAA) [[Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research]] (OAR) [[Great Lakes Environmental Research Laboratory]] (GLERL), [[Michigan State University]] (MSU), and the [[University of Michigan]] (UM). It is one of 16 NOAA Cooperative Institutes (CIs).<ref>{{cite web |title = Cooperative Institutes |publisher = NOAA Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research |date = |url = http://ci.noaa.gov/ |accessdate = 2014-04-26 |archiveurl = |archivedate = }}</ref>
The CILER research themes are: * Climate and [[Limnology|Large Lake Dynamics]] * Coastal and Nearshore Processes * Large Lake Ecosystem Structure and Function * Remote Sensing of Large Lake and Coastal Ocean Dynamics * Marine Environmental Engineering
