[[File:Urmia lake drought.webm|thumbnail|Satellite imagery from 1984 to 2014 revealing [[Lake Urmia]]'s diminishing surface area.]] A number of '''lakes''' throughout the world are '''drying''' or completely dry due to [[irrigation]] or urban use diverting inflow. [[Climate change]] is also a factor in drying some lakes.<ref name=poopo>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/07/07/world/americas/bolivia-climate-change-lake-poopo.html|title=Climate Change Claims a Lake, and an Identity|newspaper=New York Times|first=Nicholas|last=Casey|date=July 7, 2016}}</ref>
