[[Category:Lists of plants|Gibraltar Botanic Gardens]]

{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
In [[Polynesian mythology]] (specifically [[Samoa]]), '''Mafui'e''' is the god of [[earthquake]]s.

Mafui'e was also the keeper of [[fire]]. [[Ti'iti'i]], a demi-god, won the fire from him in a battle; thus, fire was brought to the people of Samoa.

[[Category:Nature gods]]
[[Category:Samoan mythology]]


