{{About|the environmental education center in Orange County, California, USA||Ecology Center (disambiguation){{!}}Ecology Center}} {{Infobox organization | name = The Ecology Center | former name = | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = File:The Ecology Center (OC) Logo 2014.png | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | | map2 = | abbreviation = TEC | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = | extinction = | type = [[Nonprofit organization]] | status = | purpose = [[Environmental education]] | headquarters = | location = 32701 Alipaz St. [[San Juan Capistrano]], CA 92675 | coords = | region_served = [[Orange County, California]] | membership = | language = | general = | leader_title = [[Executive Director]] | leader_name = Evan Marks | leader_title2 = [[Chair of the Board]] | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = [http://www.theecologycenter.org http://www.theecologycenter.org] | remarks = }}
'''The Ecology Center''' is an educational nonprofit located in [[Orange County, California]], that focuses on environmental awareness.<ref name="Ocregisterwater" /> The organization was founded by Evan Marks in 2008 on a two-acre plot that was once an 1898 homestead,<ref name="huffpostgreenfeast">{{cite web | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/xaque-gruber/the-green-feast-offers-th_b_1892223.html | title=The Green Feast Offers the Best of Orange County's Harvest for Dinner | publisher=The Huffington Post | date=19 September 2014 | accessdate=25 December 2014 | author=Gruber, Xaque}}</ref> the historical Joel Cogdon house.<ref name="Granicus 2016">{{cite web | website=Granicus | date=4 April 2016 | title=City of San Juan Capistrano City Council Meeting Agenda May 3, 2016|url=http://sjc.granicus.com/GeneratedAgendaViewer.php?view_id=3&event_id=704 | accessdate=29 April 2016}}</ref> It is well known locally for its annual Green Feast event.<ref name="huffpostgreenfeast" /><ref name="latimessomethingblah">{{cite web | url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/aug/31/news/la-dd-the-ecology-center-to-host-green-feast-on-sept-8-20120831 | title=The Ecology Center to host Green Feast on Sept. 8 | publisher=The Los Angeles Times | date=31 August 2012 | accessdate=25 December 2014 | author=Gelt, Jessica}}</ref> The Ecology Center's "Water Shed" program involves educating Orange County residents about water conservation,<ref name="Ocregisterwater">{{cite web | url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/water-633205-california-plants.html | title=A water-wise O.C. is within reach | publisher=Orange County Register | date=29 August 2014 | accessdate=25 December 2014 | author=Hoss, Shelley}}</ref> and its "Grow Your Own" program builds gardens for local schools.<ref name="ocregistergrowyourown2013">{{cite web | url=http://www.ocregister.com/articles/school-506922-garden-san.html | title=Community helps make school's garden grow | publisher=Orange County Register | date=3 May 2013 | accessdate=25 December 2014 | author=Ray, Joan}}</ref>
