The '''Wood Awards''' (until 2003 the '''Carpenters' Award''')<ref>{{cite web|title=About us|url=http://www.woodawards.com/about-us/|work=The Wood Awards|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> is a British award for working with wood. The award, which was launched in 1971, is bestowed on winners of several categories within buildings and furniture. Awards are presented in The Carpenters Hall following the decision of the architects, engineers, furniture designers / makers, timber specialists and architectural journalists who judge the competition. The Awards are sponsored by several commercial organisations and the [[Worshipful Company of Carpenters]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wood Awards|url=http://www.thecarpenterscompany.co.uk/pages/craft_activities/wood_awards/default.aspx|work=The Carpenters' Company|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>
Each year there is one winner and one "Highly Commended" project in seven categories, and a "Gold Award" for the best of the seven category winners.
==Winners== A list of winners and highly commended projects, 2008-, is available online.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.woodawards.com/winners/ | work=The Wood Awards | title=Winners | accessdate=2012-04-23}}</ref>
=== Gold Award winners, 2008- === *2008:[[Shetland Museum|New Shetland Museum & Archives]], new building<ref>{{cite web|title=New Shetland Museum & Archives|url=http://www.woodawards.com/new-shetland-museum-archives/|work=The Wood Awards|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> *2009:[[Kings Place]] Concert Hall, concert hall within larger new development<ref>{{cite web|title=Kings Place Concert Hall|url=http://www.woodawards.com/kings-place-concert-hall/|work=The Wood Awards|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> *2010:[[Stoke Newington]] Town Hall, restoration of 1930s building<ref>{{cite web|title=Stoke Newington Town Hall|url=http://www.woodawards.com/stoke-newington-town-hall/|work=The Wood Awards|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> *2011:[[Wildlife_Trust_for_Lancashire,_Manchester_and_North_Merseyside#Projects|Brockholes]] Visitor Centre, creation of new floating building on nature reserve<ref>{{cite web|title=Brockholes Visitor Centre|url=http://www.woodawards.com/brockholes-visitor-centre/|work=The Wood Awards|accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>
